commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed my chatbot to Alfred and made a skeleton greeting
Added an echo function for Alfred. As well for it to end whenever any form of 'bye' is said

Adds the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested. However, the list command is specific in the case where the text entered was something like 'list my items'

Added a few new features 1. Mark the task (This will mark the task when using "mark #"), different message will be displayed if task is already marked 2. Unmark the task (Similar to mark task feature) 3. I used functions instead so that the code is cleaner 4. Used try-catch to expect for those illegal inputs (invalid index/ out of range)

- Converted single task functions into a Task abstract class - Implemented Deadline, Event, and Todo classes extending Task - Added task-specific toString variations - Used switch statements to simplify and clean up logic
Added Automated TextUiTesting which has fixed some minor presentation bugs
